Rating: 2
The instructions are good, but as with most risotto recipes, the recipe ends up taking longer and needing more broth than in indicated - definitely have some extra broth on hand so that you don't have to finish with water! I gave this 2 fors because 1) Risotto ALWAYS starts with at least 1/2 cup dry white wine before the broth - that is how you break down the starch in the rice. After you fry the rice in the butter and onion,s stir in the wine and cook until the alcohol is gone, then start with the broth. 2) Risotto Milanese is with beef marrow broth, not chicken. At the very least, use beef or veal broth if you want a more authentic flavor, but ideally homemade broth made with a good assortment of marrow bones.

