Rating: 2
I gave the recipe a 2, but it could easily be a 3 with some small adjustments. Agreed with Brookline... double the saffron and add it sooner. And add some salt during the saute stage. I also added white wine instead of water to the broth simmer which brought out the flavor of a classic risotto. Sometimes classics are meant to be simple. Confidential to Kelly in Seattle... plain rice cooked in chicken broth is just that, not risotto. This was not a complicated recipe and it offers the basic techniques and ingredients for making true risotto (though wine is key, IMO).

