Rating: 3
What I like best about this recipe is that is very simple to follow and a good base recipe for future risotto endeavors. I took the next steps immediately. I started out by rendering some prosciuto, throwing in the shallot and (increased dosage of 8 cloves) garlic, and then deglazing pan with dry, white wine. Add drawn, clarified butter then the grains. I used the same liquifying technique until the end, when I finished the dish with a tablespoon of butter and more wine, making it truly creamy. Also, try to shave your parmisan reggiano instead of grating it. Works for me.

